This directory contains scripts to reproduce the analyses and figures from the study.

-01generate_founder_population
    code to sample and generate the founder population for simulations

-02slim_simulationA_LD_sampling
    founder population were generated by random sampling
    parameters:
    sample size: 400 (number of founder haplotypes)
    census population size: 1250
    (6)number of selection targets: 10, 100, 1000, 5000, 10000, 20000(random sampled from segregating site)
    (3)selection strength: 10, 50, 100(sum of the selection coefficients)
    (2)two extra simulations under neutrality with popsize of 1250 and 300
    linkage: LD (recombination map from Comeron et al. 2012)
    (10)Runs: 10
    (3)Supergroup: Supergroup I, II and III
    (5)Replicates within each replicates: 5
    Number of simulations: (6*3+2)*10*3*5 = 3000

-03slim_simulationA_LE_sampling
    founder population were generated by random sampling
    parameters:
    sample size: 400 (number of founder haplotypes)
    census population size: 1250
    (6)number of selection targets: 10, 100, 1000, 5000, 10000, 20000(random sampled from segregating site)
    (3)selection strength: 10, 50, 100(sum of the selection coefficients)
    (2)two extra simulations under neutrality with popsize of 1250 and 300
    linkage: LE (recombination rate 0f 0.5 per base pair)
    (10)Runs: 10
    (3)Supergroup: Supergroup I, II and III
    (5)Replicates within each replicates: 5
    Number of simulations: (6*3+2)*10*3*5 = 3000

-04slim_simulationB_LD_shuffle_genotype
    founder population were generated by shuffling the genotype
    parameters:
    sample size: 400 (number of founder haplotypes)
    census population size: 1250
    (6)number of selection targets: 10, 100, 1000, 5000, 10000, 20000(random sampled from segregating site)
    (3)selection strength: 10, 50, 100(sum of the selection coefficients)
    (2)two extra simulations under neutrality with popsize of 1250 and 300
    linkage: LD (recombination map from Comeron et al. 2012)
    (10)Runs: 10
    (3)Supergroup: Supergroup I, II and III
    (5)Replicates within each replicates: 5
    Number of simulations: (6*3+2)*10*3*5 = 3000

-05slim_simulationB_LE_shuffle_genotype
    founder population were generated by shuffling the genotype
    parameters:
    sample size: 400 (number of founder haplotypes)
    census population size: 1250
    (6)number of selection targets: 10, 100, 1000, 5000, 10000, 20000(random sampled from segregating site)
    (3)selection strength: 10, 50, 100(sum of the selection coefficients)
    (2)two extra simulations under neutrality with popsize of 1250 and 300
    linkage: LE (recombination rate 0f 0.5 per base pair)
    (10)Runs: 10
    (3)Supergroup: Supergroup I, II and III
    (5)Replicates within each replicates: 5
    Number of simulations: (6*3+2)*10*3*5 = 3000

-06slim_simulationC_LD_samplesize
    founder population were generated by random sampling
    parameters:
    (4)sample size: 400, 8000, 1200, 2500 (number of founder haplotypes)
    census population size: 1250
    (1)number of selection targets: 100 (random sampled from segregating site)
    (1)selection strength: 10 (sum of the selection coefficients)
    linkage: LD (recombination map from Comeron et al. 2012)
    (10)Runs: 10
    (3)Supergroup: Supergroup I, II and III
    (5)Replicates within each replicates: 5
    Number of simulations: 4*10*3*5 = 600
    #for sample size of 2500, every 2 haplotypes were merged to generate 1250 diploid individuals

-07empirical_results
    data and code for analyzing empirical results(experimental evolution)

-99summarize_plot
    code to summarize and plot the simulation and empirical results

